  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mental Health and Psychosocial Support (MHPSS) Assistance to Internally Displaced Persons and Affected Host Communities in the Center-North, Sahel, and East Regions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 2015, insecurity continues to increase in Burkina Faso and the resulting mass displacement has limited the population&apos;s access to basic social services, including health care. A total of 1,462 security incidents were reported from January to May 2021. Six regions are particularly affected (Sahel, Center-North, Boucle du Mouhoun, North, East and Center-East). According to CONASUR, the number of internally displaced persons (IDPs) has risen to 1,218,754, an increase of 6.19% from the last situation report in February 2021. The mental health and psychosocial support (MHPSS) needs of the affected populations are increasing exponentially as a result of the repeated security shocks in the regions affected by the humanitarian crisis. In addition to the psycho-trauma caused by the violence and losses, there is also the stress related to the difficulties in accessing basic social services, including health care. In light of these elements, IOM will implement a MHPSS project of which the objective is to strengthen and increase access to MHPSS services for IDPs and host communities in the Center-North, Sahel and East regions, targeted by the health cluster.</narrative>
  </description>
